# Cursor Rules

This repository is a Laravel 10 / PHP 8.4 enterprise real-estate platform with multi-tenant modular architecture.

## Key References
- `AGENTS.md` — repository-specific agent guidance
- `.github/agents/` — specialized agents for different development tasks
- `README.md` — full setup and platform documentation

## Quick Commands
```bash
composer install --no-interaction --prefer-dist --optimize-autoloader
npm install && npm run build
composer test && composer run-script analyse
php artisan migrate --seed
```

## Code Organization
- **Backend**: `app/Http/Controllers/`, `app/Services/`, `app/Models/`, `app/Jobs/`, `app/Events/`
- **Frontend**: `resources/views/` (Blade by domain), `resources/js/` (Vue 5 + Alpine.js)
- **Database**: `database/migrations/`, `database/seeders/`, `database/factories/`
- **Tests**: `tests/Unit/`, `tests/Feature/`
- **Routes**: `routes/api.php` (REST), `routes/web.php` (web)
- **Config**: `config/pfre.php`, `config/integrations.php`, `config/whatsapp.php`, `config/razorpay.php`

## Development Dos & Don'ts

### Do
- ✅ Use service classes in `app/Services/` for business logic
- ✅ Validate changes with `composer test` and `composer run-script analyse`
- ✅ Organize Blade templates by domain in `resources/views/`
- ✅ Use Tailwind CSS utilities instead of custom CSS
- ✅ Store generated files in `storage/app/documents/` or `storage/app/reports/`
- ✅ Reference `.env.example` for configuration patterns
- ✅ Keep REST routes aligned with `routes/api.php`

### Don't
- ❌ Hardcode configuration values (use `.env` and `config/`)
- ❌ Add business logic directly to controllers
- ❌ Modify `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` without explicit request
- ❌ Introduce new package dependencies carelessly
- ❌ Assume external services beyond those in `config/integrations.php`

## Domain Clusters (26 clusters)
CRM, Sales/Booking, Finance/Billing, GST/e-Invoice, RERA/MahaRERA, Legal/Agreements, HRMS, Payroll, Procurement, Facility Management, Society/HOA, White-Label (Clinic, School, Hotel, Retail), Warehouse, ITSM, Agriculture, Analytics, Notifications, Document Management, Configuration, BBPS, MCA, Audit.

## Specialized Agents
- **code-review** — Laravel/PHP code quality and security reviews
- **deployment** — GitHub Actions workflow and CI/CD validation
- **frontend** — Blade/Vue/Tailwind component development
- **testing** — PHPUnit/Pest test creation and coverage
- **database** — Migrations, models, seeding, schema design
- **module** — Domain-specific feature development with Indian compliance
- **environment** — Local development environment setup

See `.github/agents/` for detailed guidelines per agent.

## Frontend Stack
- **View Layer**: Laravel Blade (server-rendered) + Vue 5 (complex components) + Alpine.js (interactivity)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3.4
- **UI Libraries**: Chart.js, FullCalendar, DataTables, Leaflet, Select2
- **Build**: Vite 5 with `npm run dev` / `npm run build`

## Database & Migrations
- Use `php artisan make:model` with `-mfs` for full scaffolding
- Preserve foreign key constraints and cascading rules
- Use appropriate data types (unsignedBigInteger for IDs, decimal(18,2) for currency)
- Run `php artisan migrate` to apply; `php artisan migrate:rollback` to revert
- Seed with `php artisan db:seed` or `php artisan db:seed --class=GstRateSeeder`

## Testing
- **Unit tests** in `tests/Unit/` for services, helpers, models
- **Feature tests** in `tests/Feature/` for API endpoints, workflows
- Run with `composer test` (phpunit --testdox) or `composer test-parallel` (4 processes)
- Use Pest for modern fluent syntax or PHPUnit for compatibility
- Mock external APIs and services

## Property Storage
- Documents: `storage/app/documents/`
- Reports: `storage/app/reports/`
- Link with `php artisan storage:link`

## Compliance & Real-Estate
- **GST**: Validate GSTIN, map items to HSN/SAC, calculate IGST/CGST/SGST
- **RERA**: Track milestones, quarterly updates, complaint resolution
- **Stamp Duty**: Calculate based on property value and state rules
- **PF/ESIC/TDS**: Auto-calculate based on salary slabs
- **Multi-Tenant**: Separate data per white-label vertical

For questions, consult `.github/agents/module.agent.md` or `README.md` for domain-specific guidance.
